The GPEA facilitates the identification and ranking of significant subnetworks of defined gene sets for a given network. For p genes there is a total of N=p(p−1)/2 different gene pairs. If there are pS genes for a particular gene set (S) then the total number of gene pairs for this gene set is mS=pS(pS−1)/2. When a network G contains n interactions, of which k interactions are among genes from the given gene set S, then a p-value for the enrichment of gene pairs of this gene set S can be calculated from the following hypergeometric distribution
